The paper discusses online optimization and learning algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining applications. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions wireless communications, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of algorithms in data mining and statistical inference suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the theoretical performance guarantees of the algorithms, which is a topic covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper provides examples related to multimedia indexing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
